The Per Diem Nurse Staffing Market is witnessing significant growth due to various factors such as the increasing demand for healthcare services, rising prevalence of chronic diseases, and the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic that has put a strain on healthcare systems worldwide. Per diem nurse staffing offers flexibility to healthcare facilities by providing temporary or part-time nursing staff as needed, filling in gaps in regular staffing schedules. This on-demand staffing model helps healthcare facilities to manage fluctuating patient loads efficiently and ensures adequate patient care at all times. The market for per diem nurse staffing is expected to expand further as the healthcare industry continues to evolve and faces challenges related to workforce management and cost control.

